node.text:
Recruiting diverse talent is critical to the FBI’s success.

FBI personnel and leaders from Historically Black Colleges and Universities recently met to launch the Beacon Project, which seeks to foster relationships between the FBI and underrepresented communities. 

As part of the project, the FBI plans to boost recruiting at HBCUs and host more HBCU leaders at Citizens Academies—multi-week programs that give community leaders behind-the-scenes looks at the FBI.

Click the link in our bio to learn more about the Beacon Project.

#communityoutreach #hbcu #partnerships #recruiting

When a plane crashed in Shanksville, Pennsylvania, on September 11, 2001, FBI agents and Evidence Response Team members scoured the crash site for debris, human remains, and victims' belongings.
 
The FBI's September Artifact of the Month is a black hard hat that a responder wore for protection during the search.
 
Click the link in our bio to learn more about the FBI's investigation in Shanksville.
 
#americanhistory #artifactofthemonth #flight93 #firstresponders #history #neverforget #pennsylvania #september11 #shanksville

Click-clack! Click-clack! The FBI’s August Artifact of the Month is a Mignon 4, a mechanical index typewriter that belonged to the FBI Laboratory in the 20th century.
 
Mechanical index typewriters like the Mignon 4 had a pointer or stylus that let a typist choose a letter from the index.
 
One hand moved the pointer across the index, while the other depressed the machine’s printing key to print the letter on paper.
 
Click the link in our bio to learn more about the Mignon 4.

 #history #typewriter

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by FBI on July 27, 2021. May be an image of phone and text that says 'Phone'.

node.text:
As spectators watched the 1996 Summer Olympics, Eric Robert Rudolph planted a bomb in Centennial Olympic Park in Atlanta. The subsequent blast killed one woman and harmed more than 100 other people—and triggered a five-year manhunt for Rudolph.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Before the bomb detonated on July 27, 1996, Rudolph twice called 911 to warn about the bomb. The FBI’s July Artifact of the Month is a pay phone from the group of pay phones where Rudolph placed the calls.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The FBI placed Rudolph on the Ten Most Wanted Fugitives list on May 5, 1998. He stayed on the list until May 31, 2003, when a police officer arrested him in North Carolina.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Click the link in our bio to learn more about the case.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#artifactofthemonth #history #mostwanted #olympics #summerolympics

node.accessibility_caption: An FBI agent named Tai listens to instructors during New Operator Training School in San Juan, Puerto Rico.

node.text:
Sweating under the heat of a tropical sun, a tactical vest, and the scrutiny of her instructors, an FBI agent named Tai sprinted up a hillside in San Juan, Puerto Rico, on her first day of New Operator Training School, a 10-week program for FBI San Juan SWAT team selectees.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Tai, one of five new FBI San Juan selectees, is believed to be the first Black woman selected for an FBI SWAT team. As she trained, she wasn’t focused on the weight of the milestone—only on clearing rooms and hitting targets in synchronicity with her teammates.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
"I'm not the biggest person. I'm not as strong as some of these guys. But as long as you have perseverance, you push through it and keep going," Tai said.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#fbi #fbiagent #fbisanjuan #specialagent #swat #sanjuan #puertorico

node.text:
Director Christopher Wray visited the Pulse Memorial yesterday to honor the 49 victims who lost their lives during a shooting at the Pulse Nightclub in 2016.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
At the memorial he met with FBI Tampa Assistant Special Agent in Charge Ron Hopper, who served as the on-scene commander during the shooting.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
They reflected on the shooting near a wall that lists the names of the victims.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#orlandostrong #pulsememorial
